The structure in hoare server is 
		
		bachina.3  --->   Makefile
				  src   --------> oss.c, user.c, shared_mem.h
				   Readme
				   Logfile With the User Specified Name.

Sample Execution Format: ./master -s ChildrenCount -l logfile_Name -t program_Lifetime
========================================================================

There are 2 files named oss.c and user.c

SHared_mem.h is a header file that holds the structure of the oss clock the shmMsg.

shmMsg contains the seconds, nanoseconds, chilpid (to store the value of every child's pid) and inUse Flag. 

To run the project: cd to bachina.3 folder: make all, All the executables will be generated.

and then give the command ./master -s childCount -l logfile_name -t terminationTime

To remove the object files give command,  make clean

All the outputs for different conditions are written into the ANswers.

EVery child will write its termination time as mentioned in the project pdf to the logfile given. 

All the files are pushed to github. 
